def stock_predicator(days):
    """
    Given the stock price in the next few days (at least 3 days).
    Use dynamic programming to find to days, 
    such that buying on the earlier day and selling on the later day is the most profitable
    If all choices causes negative profits, you should return 0.
    """

    lowest = Array(n, sint)
    partial_max = Array(n, sint)
    
    lowest.assign_all(days[0])
    
    for i in range(1, n):
        lowest.assign_vector(lowest[i-1].bit_and(lowest[i-1] <= days[i]), 0)
        lowest.assign_vector(lowest[i].bit_and(lowest[i] <= days[i]), 1)
        
        partial_max.assign_vector(partial_max[i-1].bit_and(partial_max[i-1] >= days[i] - lowest[i-1]), 0)
